On the iailure oi the Jacobite movement of 1715, the impeachment os Ormond, and his resignation of the Chancellorship, the University elected his brother, the earl os Arran in his place. He was installed with great pomp on September 26, the Vico-Chancellor taking the opportunity to pronounce a panegyric on the house of Butler, and to suggest that in order to acknowledge its obligations to that family, the University had elected Arran to succeed the exiled Ormond.
